Smart contract library of mathematical functions operating with signed
 64.64-bit fixed point numbers.  Signed 64.64-bit fixed point number is
 basically a simple fraction whose numerator is signed 128-bit integer and
 denominator is 2^64.  As long as denominator is always the same, there is no
 need to store it, thus in Solidity signed 64.64-bit fixed point numbers are
 represented by int128 type holding only the numerator.

_blackScholesPrice(int128,int128,int128,.notice: calculate the price of an option using the Black-Scholes model

params.spot64x64: 64x64 fixed point representation of spot price
params.strike64x64: 64x64 fixed point representation of strike price
params.timeToMaturity64x64: 64x64 fixed point representation of duration of option contract (in years)
params.varianceAnnualized64x64: 64x64 fixed point representation of annualized variance

returns._0: 64x64 fixed point representation of Black-Scholes option price

params.isAbove: whether to the user bets the price will stay above this strike or not
params.spot64x64: 64x64 fixed point representation of spot price
params.strike64x64: 64x64 fixed point representation of strike price
params.timeToMaturity64x64: 64x64 fixed point representation of duration of option contract (in years)
params.varianceAnnualized64x64: 64x64 fixed point representation of annualized variance

returns._0: 64x64 fixed point representation of Black-Scholes option price

params.impliedVol: uint256 representation of annualized impliedVol with a factor of 1e4
params.period: uint256 representation of duration of option contract (in seconds)
params.spot: uint256 representation of spot price with a factor of 1e8
params.strike: uint256 representation of strike price with a factor of 1e8

returns._0: uint256 representation of Black-Scholes option price with a factor of 1e8
